questions.text: Manager's Note

E.raw_value: Shown on Manager Dashboard; GIA Marker

questions.text: Letters in blue mean the data is pulled via API to our system.
If cells are outlined in orange and the letters are blue, this means it's a date/time timestamp from XactAnalysis.
If cells are outlined in orange and the letters are light purple, this means it's a timer due date/time based on the data from XactAnalysis.
The blue background represents an alarm which is an important stopping point in the claim

The beige background represents cells throughout this process to reassign the claim. Additionally, if a cell includes the phrase "What is the Plan of Action?" this is also an opportunity to reassign the claim.
The pink strip with grey background represent a sub form if a timestamp is either missing after the due date or a timestamp date/time is changed.
